    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-06T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="782"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/1125: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Myers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-06T23:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 6, 1939—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 6—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. Reference my 80, July 22, 1 p.m. According to a notification from the
                    Japanese Consul General, the Pearl River will be reopened to navigation as from
                    August 7 under the same conditions as existed prior to its closure on July
                    27.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, Hong Kong.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
